{
  "type": "root",
  "children": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Hoi Chan is a Hong Kong-born, New Orleans-based illustrator whose work is deeply influenced by nature and personal emotions. Drawing from his observations of the natural world, he intricately weaves organic elements with the complexities of the human mind."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Having lived in both Hong Kong and New Orleans, Chan’s artistic expression is shaped by the tropical environments of these two locales. The humidity-laden breezes, lush vegetation, and abundant rainfall inform his distinctive color palette and fluid, inviting shapes. His work not only reflects the external world around him but also serves as a visual extension of his emotions and lived experiences."
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
